<subSubSection pageId="2" pageNumber="407" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1436,291,712]" pageId="2" pageNumber="407">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,616,640]" pageId="2" pageNumber="407">Etymology.</emphasis>
Patronym, for Mr. James Zigras, and –mecia, a common suffix for ant genera. In acknowledgment of Mr. Zigras’ generosity in loaning this and many other rare and scientifically valuable specimens from his collection of Burmese amber.
</paragraph>
